article.headline: Radford 75, Campbell 68
article.story: RADFORD, Va. (AP) -- Kenny Thomas scored 23 points and Joey Lynch-Flohr added 15 and nine rebounds Saturday night, leading Radford to a 75-68 victory against Campbell. The Highlanders (4-6) led 64-44 with 4:36 to play after a free throw by Thomas, then held on comfortably despite being outscored 24-11 the rest of the way. Campbell (2-5) was led by Jonathan Rodriguez with 27 points and 13 rebounds. Cole Wilder added 13 points and Martell McDuffy had 11 for Radford, which outscored Campbell 28-13 from the free throw line. Reggie Bishop added 12 points for Campbell.
